    {
      "id": "841506372381619",
      "score": 1,
      "review_title": "It sucks (imo)",
      "review_description": "Most money-hungry games try to hide that their purpose is to make money, but this one doesn’t even try.\nBuy buttons are everywhere. Six dollars for a fling stick, thirty for a fake moderator tag (just a cosmetic tag on your head that says “moderator,” it doesn’t make you one), thirty to go invisible, and worst of all, a one-hundred-dollar kick hammer.\n\nIt feels like this game is designed to take advantage of kids who don’t know better. I’ve seen other reviews saying people bought these “mod menus” but never received them. The game also uses stolen assets. On top of that, the controls barely work — I feel like I’m constantly fighting gravity while sticking to random surfaces, while others move smoothly.\n\nYou might enjoy it if you really want to, but in my opinion it’s a 1 out of 10. The game itself is bad, and the microtransactions make it worse. Don’t waste your time or money.",
